### 💡 Next Steps: How to publish it live
After creating your repository and uploading your `portfolio_fixed.html` file:
1. Go to your repository **Settings**.
2. Scroll down on the left sidebar and click on **Pages**.
3. Under *Build and deployment*, change the branch from `None` to `main` (or `master`), select `/root`, and click **Save**.
4. GitHub will give you a live link to your portfolio within a few minutes! 

*(Note: For GitHub Pages to open your site automatically as the homepage, it is highly recommended to rename `portfolio_fixed.html` to `index.html` inside your repository).*
